    "Based on the traditional neighbor set, each neighbor node in the set is associated with a timestamp to form a pair.",
    "It indicates that at time, node is connected to node.",
    "It is required that the timestamp corresponding to a neighboring node is smaller than the current timestamp.",
    "In other words, represents the collection of adjacent nodes resulting from events occurring prior to time.",
    "Hawkes processest [t, t + ∆) tIntroduced by Hawkes in 1971 [13], the Hawkes process is a mathematical model for time-sequenced events."
